				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
					<div data-elementor-type="wp-post" data-elementor-id="29819" class="elementor elementor-29819" data-elementor-post-type="tdser">
				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-f87a5ca e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent" data-id="f87a5ca" data-element_type="container">
					<div class="e-con-inner">
				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-258b390 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-id="258b390" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="heading.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
			<h2 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">UNIFORM</h2>		</div>
				</div>
				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-f0faf65 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="f0faf65" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
							<p><strong>Uniform policy:</strong></p><p>Students are required to wear school uniforms everyday during the week. The only exceptions are the last Fridays of each month, students are able to wear their own outfit &#8211; please note that these outfits must be appropriate with the educational environment (no short skirts/shorts which are 5cm and above knee height)</p>						</div>
